@endnode

@node "Require" " MV Comment - Requirements"
@next "install"
@prev "disclaim"
    
                      @{b}Door requirements@{ub}
                      ----------------- 

You need Amiga OS and DayDream 1.27 or higher (door is using HideCursor
& ShowCursor functions of dreamdoor.library, and those functions
are implemented in version 1.27 and later), and RoboWriter utility
(included with DayDream distribution) somewhere in your PATH.



@endnode

@node "Install" " MV Comment - Instalation "
@next "Features"
@prev "Require"


 It is highly recomended to use supplied INSTALL script for instaling 
MV COMMENT Door. To use it, simply unpack archive (you have to extract 
archive with enabled "Extract files with full path" option!) on any device,
enter this diretory from shell and type INSTALL. (make sure that Doors: 
directory is already assigned, otherwise install script will fail!)

If operation is finished succesfuly, install script will write following
message :
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
        Mad Virgin COMMENT door V1.00a for DayDream BBS - AMIGA !
                                                               (01.05.1997)

 INSTALATION OK !

 PLEASE READ THE DOCS !!!!
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
and return you to main prompt.

After that, add in your DayDream folowing lines to EXTERNALCOMMANDS.DAT
+
DOOR_COMMAND.. C
DOOR_TYPE..... 1
DOOR_SECURITY. 5
DOOR_EXECUTE.. Doors:MV/Comment/MV-Comment %N
DOOR_CONFS1... XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
DOOR_CONFS2... XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
+


@endnode

@node "Features" " MV Comment - Features "
@next Config
@prev "Install"

MV Comment allow you to make list of up to 15 important users (you, 
your cosysops, etc...) , and then any user may simply leave comments.
MV Comment also fix problems about 100 comments in 100 conferences 
(message bases) - simply MV Comment will put all comments into MSG Base
you specify in your @{"Config" Link Config}.


@endnode

@node Config " MV Comment - Configuration"
@next "User"
@prev "Features"

                  @{bg shine}»»»»»»»» CONFIGURATION ««««««««««@{bg back}

   The MV Comment Door have only one config file located at
   Doors:MV/Comment/MV-Comment.CFG

!MAIN_DATA 
@{"COMM_CONF." Link Config-Comm_Conf } 1
@{"COMM_BASE." Link Config-Comm_Base } 1
@{"MIN_LEVEL." Link Config-Min_Level } 10
@{"ALLANSI..." Link Config-ALLANSI } Y
@{"SELCOL...." Link Config-SELCOL } [37;44m
@{"UN_SELCOL." Link Config-UN_SELCOL } [37;40m
@{"DESC_COL.." Link Config-DES_COL } [33m
@{"MARKER...." Link Config-MARKER } -=>
~
!NAME_DATA (max lenght 25 chars)
@{"Name01...." Link Config-Name01} Teorist
Name02.... Lilith
Name03.... FreaK
Name04.... Phuzzy Logik
Name05.... -
Name06.... -
Name07.... -
Name08.... -
Name09.... -
Name10.... -
Name11.... -
Name12.... -
Name13.... -
Name14.... -
Name15.... -
~
!COMMENT_DATA (Max lenght 30 chars)
@{"Comm01...." Link Config-comm01} SySoP
Comm02.... CoSys
Comm03.... ALife SysOp & EroS CoSys
Comm04.... CoSys
Comm05.... -
Comm06.... -
Comm07.... -
Comm08.... -
Comm09.... -
Comm10.... -
Comm11.... -
Comm12.... -
Comm13.... -
Comm14.... -
Comm15.... -
~
END OF COMMENT.CFG FILE !
@endnode


@node Config-Comm_Conf " MV Comment - Configuration Comm_Conf "

COMM_CONF

Number of conference to put comments in!

@endnode

@node Config-Comm_Base " MV Comment - Configuration Comm_Base "

COMM_BASE

Number of message base to put comments in!

@endnode


@node Config-Min_Level " MV Comment - Configuration Min_level "

MIN_LEVEL

Minimal access level to see MV-Comment menu.
Is user with lover access level enter MV-Comment, it will be automaticaly
promprted to enter comment to SysOp (First user from NAME_DATA list)

@endnode


@node Config-ALLANSI " MV Comment - Configuration ALLANSI"

ALLANSI

Y/N switch weather to use ANSI position commands in NON_ANSI display
mode or not.


@endnode

@node Config-SELCOL " MV Comment - Configuration SELCOL "

SELCOL 

ANSI colour sequence to use for Selected username in list.

@endnode


@node Config-UN_SELCOL " MV Comment - Configuration UN_SELCOL "

UN_SELCOL 

ANSI colour sequence to use for NOT-Selected usernames in list.

@endnode

@node Config-DES_COL " MV Comment - Configuration DES_COL "

DES_COL

ANSI colour sequence to use for username comments in list.

@endnode

@node Config-MARKER " MV Comment - Configuration MARKER"

MARKER

Maximum 3 ASCII characters which will be used as pointer in list
(usefull especialy for Mono displays with ANSI Support)

@endnode


@node Config-Name01 " MV Comment - NAME_DATA configs"

Name01

List of maximum 15 user names which will be show in menu.
You have to enter username EXACTLY as it is on your board, becouse
this name will be used as To: field in saved comment.

If you want less than 15 names, simply put - instead name.
When MV-Comment reach first '-' as username it will not show any
entry below!

@endnode


@node Config-Comm01 " MV Comment - COMMENT_DATA configs"

Comm01

In this fields you may enter description for each username in Comment list.

@endnode



